<TITLE> CA requests G8's help to overcome tariff barriers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 12 (bdnews24.com)--Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed has requested G8 leaders to help least developed countries overcome tariff and non-tariff barriers in developed markets. Fakhruddin asked for market access of LDC products "without discrimination". Foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury Tuesday said that the chief adviser had written separate letters to the heads of the G8 nations on behalf of the WTO LDCs Consultative Group of which Bangladesh is the chair. "The chief adviser asked for market access benefits for all products from all LDCs without discrimination," Iftekhar said. Fakhruddin has made the request ahead of the G8 summit to take place in Tokyo in July. "The issue of environmental vulnerability of most LDCs due to global warming and climate change was also underscored," the foreign adviser said. The G8 group comprises the eight most industrialised nations in the world. The chief adviser wrote separate letters to US president George W Bush, Russian president Vladimir Putin, British prime minister Gordon Brown, French president Nicolas Sarkozy, German chancellor Angela Merkel, Canadian prime minister Stephen Harper, Japanese prime minister Yasuo Fukuda and Italian prime minister Romano Prodi, bd
